Interface Gene

All Superinterfaces:
java.lang.Comparable<XIdObject>, XIdObject
All Known Subinterfaces:
ARTLinkGene, ARTNodeGene, LinkGene, NodeGene
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractGene, AbstractLinkGene, AbstractNodeGene, ARTLinkGeneImpl, ARTNodeGeneImpl, LinkGeneImpl, NodeGeneImpl
public interface Gene
extends XIdObject

The Gene interface describes the basic genetic unit in the NEAT algorithm. A Gene has an associated Innovation object, which is descriptive of where it belongs in the genome as a whole. It also has a FieldMap and a Configuration, used to specify the attributes specific to the gene.

Author:
Luis Guimbarda
